column4: "dougmck@pipeline.com.au. This was a favourite of Bill Evans  - I tried to capture some of the feel of his playing - bass and drums especially on the slow middle chorus play very freely - as a kind of counterpoint to the piano. One other 'trademark' sound\012"
"Chord is ever so slightly 'rolled' from the top down - one of Bill Evans' trademark sounds"
"More Bill Evans type playing of chords - the 2 notes (6ths) are not played at the same time - the lower one is played very slightly after the upper one"
"This phrase is a descending arpeggio - 2nd inversion triad (C Maj) with an upper neighbour (F) "

column5: an ascending diminished scale with a 'flourish' at the beginning using neighbouring tones on the 5th and 7th "

column4: "Same 2nd inversion C Maj triad with upper neighbour F as before"
